31081.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"csb2b","text":"Transfer all the data frills from the flow cytometer to the appropriate computer directory","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dv168","text":"This directory must be available to the MPLEX software. The MPLEX software requires a license file to be placed in the same directory as the EXE file before the software will operate. The software is only available to academic and non-profit institutions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"e94tb","text":"Data files must be in FCS format (see FCS data standard here). It is critical that the instrument that collected the files name them properly. So for example, each well of a plate, must have somewhere within the filename a location address, e.g. A1, B2, F12, etc. It can be in any position of the filename, the sofware will find each file and associate it with the correct well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4ng89","text":"All files must be properly identified by the row and column ID of the 96 or 384 well plate with at minimum a format which has in the file name A1, A2, etc.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"30hhq","text":"All the FCS files must be in the same directory. MPLEX ONLY loads directories (although it is possible to load individual files and place them into any desired well if you want to)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"df1ue","text":"The next step is to assign GATES to the light scatter. The scatter without gates looks like this: (scatterMPLEX.gif) It should be noted that there are almost always \"satelite\" beads that are doublets and sometimes form small populations that are not the key populations and these should be ignored. The best technique for determining the correct location of any bead population is to simply take a single bead and run a few hundred on the cytometer and identify its proper location. This can be done directly from the original bead populations and does not require you to perform any assay or incubations. You are only checking the bead locations.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"inb4","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2noks","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"b9msu","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"75D9FC2022D511EA8BDCE353CFEC0C56","height":386,"id":53160,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/gif","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"scatterMPLEX.GIF","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/private/59846f92efe7b499ef3e488f471e782d851ed800fd6030a799761f1bcda0934f/bv7ibarkf.gif","shadow":false,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/private/59846f92efe7b499ef3e488f471e782d851ed800fd6030a799761f1bcda0934f/bv7ibarkf.gif","width":626}}}}
